alth problems. A: Yes. Heat increases dehydration risk. Allergens trigger itching. Outdoor debris can irritate paws and ears. Seasonal awareness reduces avoidable illness. Preventive care supports year-round comfort. A: Most adult pets benefit from annual exams. Seniors and pets with chronic conditions often require visits every six months. Routine monitoring detects early issues before they escalate.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3b65229729dfc017\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"2 days ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.petcarevetclinic.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"468e96604a241f88\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n'Spying' on Pets with Clients\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"468e96604a241f88\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.aaha.org/trends-magazine/march-2024/spying-on-pets-with-clients/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1f5025af04cd522f\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThese changes can be monitored and compared as the pet ages and lifestyle changes. Home security cameras can be utilized to collect pet behavior data. Pets live in a human-centric world with lifestyles curated by their caregivers. Given their unique sensory perception, differing needs, and inability to communicate verbally, conflict and behavior complaints are not uncommon.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1f5025af04cd522f\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"January 10, 2025\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.aaha.org\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"pet behavior monitor user complaints problems","provider":"brave","count":5,"tookMs":1851,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"brave","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"be21dac3d6c4b9fd\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nMaven Pet Health Tracker | 24/7 Monitoring | Pet Smart Collar\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"be21dac3d6c4b9fd\">>>","url":"http